phrases: In the end, the majority decided that Steel Lady Nanase was fiction.
Sakuragawa Rikka's schemes have been rejected.
Well, well...
We have received an email.
It is from Rikka-san.
Huh?!
This is Kuro-senpai's laptop, so I am sure she knew his email address.
Rikka
Sakuragawa Kuro
Subject No Subject
Kuro, Kotoko-san, You win this time.
See you again.
So she knew that it was you two who were getting in her way.
I guess that makes sense.
The only one who could get in the way of her ability to determine the future
is Kuro-kun, who has the same ability.
And she is the only one who would do something like this.
Honestly, Rikka-san.
I have asked you so many times not to call me by my first name.
Do you not like Kotoko?
It is hard for me to say myself, and I think others have a hard time, as well.
And because of that, it does not feel right when people say it.
That is why I have Kuro-senpai call me by my surname.
Oh, so that is why he calls you by your surname even though you are going out.
Did you doubt that we were actually dating?
I told you that from the start.
More importantly, Rikka-san said this time.
I am sure she intends to make another monster of the imagination.
This is not enough to dissuade her, either.
Why is Rikka-san doing this?
People's imaginations hold an endless amount of potential.
They can create yokai, ghosts, and demons.
We give life to monsters without even realizing it.
And if that is true, then anything is possible.
You might even be able to create a god.
B-But that is...
That is not an answer at all.
What is the point in creating a god?
Good work out there!
After dying and coming back to life so many times, I am sure you are out of energy.
You must replenish your nutrients at once.
Eat this.
You are the one who needs nourishment.
You created so many possibilities and futures,
and had me grasp them.
I know how much energy that takes.
Now, do not be like that.
Just eat.
I am sure it will put Saki-san at ease, too, if she sees you eating like a human.
I only ask that I get to partake of your banana later, Kuro-senpai.
Please... I am begging you...
Do not make vulgar jokes like that at a time like this.
Oh, blessed day!
That accursed Steel Lady is gone!
Hooray!
Hooray!
Hooray!
Hooray!
Hooray for our lady!
Let us hurry back home.
Aw...
Why not let me enjoy the praise a little longer?
It looks like Saki-san's about to pass out.
I am sorry, Saki-san.
If I would tried to stop Rikka-san earlier,
we might have been able to deal with this before Terada-san was killed.
I am sure neither of you could have
predicted that something like this would happen.
So it was out of all of our hands.
Your ability to determine the future
is not exactly powerful enough to save everyone.
There are very few people who believe in
and speak of the spectre Steel Lady Nanase anymore.

It is as if they are from an alternative reality different from our own.
Almost like a story we would see on TV or in the newspaper.
Which means it is unlikely that anyone would actually
bump into anyone involved in Nanase Karin's case in real life.
This drama was resolved within the Internet.
The story would be sullied if anyone pursued it in reality.
Even if people continued to embellish this story and talk of it quietly,
they would still deny Steel Lady Nanase's existence.
That is how much care she put into all of this.
I am never making her my enemy...
As for the police,
they apparently intend to look into the possibility that
Nanase Karin's body was someone else's,
and find out who created the site.
Even if they looked into it,
there is no proof that the body belonged to someone else.
I am sure the brass will eventually decide that they
were just being led around by the rumors
on the Internet, and that Nanase Karin did indeed die in January of this year.
We will not find out what happened to Nanase Karin and her family.
The killer who murdered Detective Terada has disappeared.
Back to business as usual.
This is my life.
Saki-san.
Uh, wait.
Where is Iwanaga-san?
She is still asleep.
Huh?
But it is been a full day.
She overworked her brain all day yesterday,
so I figured this would happen.
You should act a little more concerned.
I will, when it is necessary.
You wanted to know about Rikka-san, right?
Yes.
What is she after?
I asked Iwanaga-san, but she just changed the subject.
I have resigned myself to the fact that I have this body and this ability.
For now, it seems that I am still growing and aging normally,
so while I cannot die from an accident or injury,
I am hopeful that I can still die of old age.
If I die, I will not be able to use my ability to determine the future,
and I am not usually put in situations dangerous enough to kill me,
so I think I will be able to live a normal life.
Normal...
Normal, huh?
But that is not the case for Rikka-san.
She is trying to use her ability as much as she can
to return to being a normal human being.
Is that even possible?
Even if she used her ability to go through all the possibilities...
A future where she is a normal human being?
How could such a miracle happen?
That is right.
Rikka-san was at the university hospital
trying to find out if it was medically possible to return her back to normal.
In the end, there were no possibilities based on logical methods.
She decided she would have to grasp the future she wanted herself.
And then what happened?
People's imaginations might even be able to create a god.
So Rikka-san is trying to create a monster of the imagination
that possesses the ability to turn her back into a normal human being...
She is trying to create something that has godly powers like that?
I am quite certain that Rikka-san
will do whatever it takes.
I do not know what she is thinking.
She wants to be normal, but does the most abnormal things.
Even before she consumed the flesh of the kudan and mermaid,
I cannot help but think that she may have always been a monster at heart.
But Kuro-kun, you still love Rikka-san, do not you?
I cannot shake that, either.
So what will you do now?
Rikka-san's going to continue trying to make a monster, right?
Iwanaga will not let that happen.
No matter what the reason may be,
a person or monster trying to create a monster for their own desires
goes against the natural order.
That is basically why she gave up her right eye and left leg.
So I guess you are not going to let it slide either, then.
As much as I hate to say it...
Did you delete my number from your phone?
Yes.
Iwanaga kept nagging me about it.
Even if she did not nag, you cannot keep my number.
She is the type who would let that bother her.
Yes, but...
It is not like we could ever start over again, Saki-san.
Yeah.
Seeing you after all this time just confirmed that it is impossible.
I am okay with sitting across the table from you,
but I would be a bit hesitant to touch you.
I am sorry.
No, it is also my fault for keeping it a secret.
Make sure you take care of Iwanaga-san.
I do.
She is always been oblivious of danger.
In a way, she is more fearless than I am.
She is been hurt more than a few times
while trying to resolve conflicts between monsters.
To be honest, I did not want to involve Iwanaga in the matter with Rikka-san.
I was trying to take care of it before she got involved.
But after this incident, Rikka-san realizes that Iwanaga is the biggest obstacle
that stands in her way.
Which means that Rikka-san might go after Iwanaga next.
That never even crossed my mind...
Considering what Rikka-san is capable of,
if she thinks Iwanaga-san is in her way...
So that is why you were looking for Rikka-san without telling Iwanaga-san?
Though I am sure if you had told her,
Iwanaga-san would have tried to get involved.
I will not let Iwanaga die.
Because she is someone who deserves to be happy.
Now I can finally get some closure.
I am pretty sure I will never see him again.
Are you sure I can have this bike?
Iwanaga bought this so she could travel around the city.
It would be a pain to take it back home, so Iwanaga wanted you to have it.
Oh, and she told the monsters
around the city not to appear in front of you anymore.
Thanks...
Not sure if that makes me feel any better...
See you!
I still get scared at night.
But...
There is someone out there protecting the order of things.
I am sure the world will not end up a crazy mess after all.
She Who Defends Order
I messed up again!
I keep messing up over and over again!
I slept for a day and a half...
Oh, it is still only six.
I feel quite refreshed, for only sleeping about four hours...
9/6 (Tues)
September 6th?
I was completely knocked out for 28 hours?!
I gave Kuro-senpai and Saki-san so much time to spend alone together!
This is the biggest mistake of my life!
Iwanaga?
Huh, she is not here?
Senpai!
Ow!
Ow!
Oh, she is just in the bath.
Take your time in there.
If you are still tired, we can probably stay another ni
You reek of Saki-san!
That is impossible.
But I know you saw her!
Yeah, because you said you wanted to give her the bicycle.
So I thought the sooner the better.
And I had some time on my hands.
Well, yes, I did, but...
How did you get her contact info?
On the way back in the car the other night, we exchanged numbers...
But I already deleted her number.
I will not be seeing Saki-san again.
That is not the problem here!
You need to dry off first.
You are going to catch a cold.
Wait!
What are you doing?!
I do not have another clean shirt!
This is not funny!
Just give in!
Thanks for everything.
Thank you for staying with us.
You are still mad?
I am not.
I am just reflecting.
I should have woken up after 12 hours.
I am going to work on increasing my strength and vitality.
Should we take a taxi?
The station is not that far.
Let us just walk.
It looks like it is going to rain.
For Pedestrians and Bicycles
Am I going to have to sit around on a bench with you as you nap again?
Even I could not possibly doze off after sleeping for 28 hours!
Senpai.
I am sure Rikka-san will not make her next move immediately,
but I am going to tell all of the yokai and monsters across the country
to let me know if they see anything.
I would rather not go through all that trouble again.
The best way to take care of this is to find her and talk to her in person.
Also, if you find out anything new, please do not act without telling me.
I will see what I can do.
Honestly...
Iwanaga...
If you know about the Kuebiko, then you also know about Princess Iwanaga.
Yes, from the Kojiki.
It sounds just like my surname, so of course I know about it.
Princess Iwanaga.
The older sister of Princess Konohana-no-Sakuya.
They were both given in marriage to Ninigi-no-Mikoto,
descendant of the high god.
But Ninigi-no-Mikoto only married Princess Konohana-no-Sakuya
and sent Princess Iwanaga back home.
That enraged their father, Oyamatsumi.
There was a reason I gave you both sisters!
Just as the iwa, or rock, in Princess Iwanaga's name suggests,
she was able to give life as eternal as rocks
that never change month to month, year after year.
But because Ninigi-no-Mikoto did not marry her and returned her to her father,
he and his progeny were granted short lives that scattered like flowers on trees.
They became mortal.
Then you get it, right?
I am immortal, so I do not belong
with Princess Konohana-no-Sakuya.
I need Princess Iwanaga.
I am sure you thought that was smooth,
but you know why Princess Iwanaga was returned home, do not you?
Let us not worry about the minor details.
It is not minor at all!
Princess Iwanaga was sent home because she was ugly!
You could not have used a worse metaphor for a girl!
But you are prettier than any flower, so I have not sent you back anywhere.
Either way,
it is never good to judge anyone by their physical appearance.
You are just an amalgamation of a mermaid and a kudan.
Stop trying to sound like you are so cool.
Senpai, will you be staying at my place tonight?
My parents have been wanting to see you.
Well, I do need to apologize for putting them out.
There is no need to be so formal.
You can think of them and our house as your own.
I cannot.
I cannot let you fence me in just yet.
Do you still think you can get away from me?
In this world, there are yokai, ayakashi,
spectres, demons,
mononoke, and ghosts.
Creatures with those names exist, just like everything else.
There is reason that transcends reason,
and logical and illogical go hand in hand.
But there is no reason to be afraid.
There is an order to all things.
No matter what methods Rikka-san tries to use,
no matter how much she wants to create a new god,
I will protect that order, regardless.
Even if I have to create a rational fiction...
or a fiction that transcends the truth.
I will defend this world from that gap between truth and fiction.
Kuro-senpai.
I believe today will be a lovely day.
The End
